{"body": "It would iterate each of the arguments are check them against `obj`, using `===`. Here's an implementation:\r\n\r\n    require 'active_support/core_ext/object/blank'\r\n\r\n    class Object\r\n      def matches?(*args)\r\n        args.find { |arg| arg === self }.present?\r\n      end\r\n    end\r\n\r\n    'foo'.matches?('foo', /bar/) # => true\r\n    'bar'.matches?('foo', /bar/) # => true\r\n    'barkeeper'.matches?('foo', /bar/) # => true\r\n    'zookeeper'.matches?('foo', /bar/) # => false", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/632559", "created_at": "2010-12-23T18:10:12Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/138#issuecomment-632559", "updated_at": "2010-12-23T18:10:12Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 138, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jonleighton", "type": "User", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523868a5bd3543c1510129a9"}, "id": 632559, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/138"}
